Principal Deputy National Security Advisor Jon Finer, along with National Security Council Senior Director for Africa Dana Banks and Deputy Assistant Secretary for African Affairs Michael Gonzalez, will be traveling to Nigeria, Equatorial Guinea, and Mauritania for official meetings next week. In Nigeria, Mr. Finer will emphasize the importance of the U.S. relationship with Africa's largest democracy and discuss democratic progress, the rule of law, and addressing climate change and terrorism. He will also highlight the U.S. commitment to global health security, as a significant number of Pfizer vaccines have been donated to Nigeria. In Equatorial Guinea, discussions will focus on maritime security in the Gulf of Guinea, while in Mauritania, both delegations will address the shared commitment to combating terrorist groups and other mutual interests.